I want to create a recurring event that deploys every 4th Wednesday of the month.  I created a recurring monthly event, initially scheduled for the 28th of the month, and I then tried to move each instance of the event to the appropriate Wednesday date for the month.

In some instances, there were no problems.  In other instances, I would get duplicate events:  One on the original date (28th) and one on the appropriate date (See AL_LIN_Reschedule1.jpg).  

However, If I try to remove the incorrect instance on the 28th (see AL_LIN_Delete2.jpg), both events are removed from the calendar.  It is only obvious that the correct event is also removed from the calendar complete when the calendar is refreshed (see AL_LIN_Reschedule2.jpg).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-48683].
  {panel}

h3. Step to reproduce the issue, 
# Create 100 calendar with the name "default testxxx cal" with xxx from 001 to 100. 
# Click on the button: "Add Calendar >> Add Existing Calendar >> Search for other Calendar" in the text box type:
{noformat}
default test001
{noformat} 
or
{noformat}
default test001 cal
{noformat}

h3. Expected behaviour:
Only the calendar "default test001 cal" should show. 

h3. Actual behaviour:
All 100 calendar are loaded in the search output, sometime need to scroll down a few page to find it as only 10 items is loaded par page. 

h3. Workaround solution: 
Use the double quote to protect the text should limit the scope: 
{noformat}
"default test001 cal"
{noformat}

